    <article>
    <h2><i>Tartar salmon</i></h2>
    <img src="html_fundamentals/IMG_7492.JPG" alt="picture of tartar salmon">
    <h3>Ingridients:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>400 gr salmon fillets</li>
      <li>4-5 shallot onions</li>
      <li>2 tbs white wine vinegar</li>
      <li>200 gr heavy cream</li>
      <li> 100 gr sour cream</li>
      <li> 1 1/2 cup of chopped dill</li>
      <li>1 lemon for plating</li>
     </ul>
    <h3>Method</h3>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Preparing tartar salmon</strong>
        <br><em>Chop salmon and shallots finely into small cubes. Mix chopped salmon and shallots with 1 cup of finely chopped dill. 
        Add some pepper and salt.</em></li>
          
      <li><strong>Prepare <span lang="fr">creme fraiche</span></strong><br>
        <em>Mix in another bowl heavy cream, sour cream, white wine vinegar and half cup of chopped dill. Add some salt and pepper
        </em>  </li>
       <li><strong>Plating</strong><br>
         <em>Apply 3-4 table spoons of <span lang="fr">creme fraiche </span> onto the plate. Put ring (a bit smaller in diameter of applied creme fraiche) in the center of<span lang="fr">creme fraiche </span>and then put tartar salmon inside. Remove the ring. Add splash of lemon juice.</em> </li>
      <li>Enjoy!</li>
    </ol>
      </article>
